-- Algerian Negotiations on Djezzy Continue, Finance Minister Says
-- B y   S a l a h   S l i m a n i
-- 2012-09-03T16:28:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/algerian-negotiations-on-djezzy-continue-finance-minister-says.html
The Algerian government is still in
talks to buy the 51 percent stake of mobile phone operator
Djezzy held by Russian telecommunications company  VimpelCom
Ltd. (VIP) , Finance Minister  Karim Djoudi  said.  “We will inform the public of the nature of the agreement
between the parties at the conclusion of the discussions,”
Djoudi told reporters today in Algiers.  Algeria is looking to purchase the stake in Djezzy held by
Russia’s VimpelCom Ltd., the world’s sixth-largest wireless
operator by subscribers, which merged with Orascom Telecom last
year. The parties have yet to agree on a price.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saleh Slimani via Cairo at 
 sslimani2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden in Dubai at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  